Description: Jackson RR Concorde JS32-CD - Snow white with Gold Hardware These models are much more in line with Randy's original white prototype concorde due to the bigger body and wider "wingspan" than the typical RR models, Neck is also inset in to the body like Randy's first concorde. I bought this used several months ago and only played it a few times, In same condition as when I recieved it. Guitar has minor cosmetic flaws as pictured - slight discoloration of back of wing tip, small chips on horn tips (easy touch up fix), cosmetic spot on neck past 24th fret (another easy touch up fix) and a spot on volume knob. Other than that it looks and sounds great. When purchased it did not come with a whammy bar - I have added an aftermarket bar in matching gold finish, not a perfect plush fit but it gets the job done just fine. Thanks for looking ! "The original and iconic Jackson Concorde triangular shape arrives in JS Series form with modern design elements to meet the needs of today’s high performance players. Loaded with classic Jackson specs, tone and style, the Concorde JS32 offers tremendous bang for the buck. This sleek turbojet axe features a 25.5 in. scale length, offset V-shape body crafted out of poplar, one-piece bolt-on maple neck with graphite reinforcement and scarf joint, newly designed scalloped shredder’s heel to allow for comfortable access to the upper frets, and Jackson’s pointed 6-in-line headstock. Its 12 -16 in. compound radius blackwood fingerboard has single-ply white binding, 24 jumbo frets and pearloid sharkfin inlays. Also features dual Jackson high-output humbucking pickups with three-way toggle switching and master volume and tone controls, Floyd Rose double-locking tremolo, and Jackson sealed die-cast tuners.
